ything specific, so I'm thinking about whether I should remove or delete a file. The generic file might be part of a scaffold, but there’s a one-to-one rule regarding generated active class files, which complicates things. I might leave it alone for now. I should also mention that I won’t run tests as per instruction and clarify that untracked metadata hasn’t been touched.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a dedicated Scala test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- Added `CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeTest.scala` under:\n  `tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/src/test/scala/com_github_plokhotnyuk_jsoniter_scala/jsoniter_scala_macros_3/`\n\nWhat it covers:\n- Runtime Scala macro compilation through `JsonCodecMaker.make`.\n- A precompiled Scala fixture object referenced from the macro config, exercising:\n  - `retrieveRuntimeModule`\n  - module `Class.forName`\n  - module `MODULE$` field lookup/get\n- Scala object `val` access through an accessor method, exercising:\n  - `retrieveRuntimeField`\n  - `Class#getMethod`\n  - `Method#invoke`\n- Java public-field-backed mapper access, exercising:\n  - `retrieveRuntimeField`\n  - fallback `Class#getField`\n  - `Field#get`\n\nThe test catches Native Image unsupported-feature errors for the runtime compilation path and rethrows all other errors.\n\nPer instruction, I did not compile or run the tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0de9e442508f38ed016a1155552418819688dcc637ec39f15f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 486, "output": 1564, "cacheRead": 64512, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 66562, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779520831133, "responseId": "resp_0de9e442508f38ed016a11554011388196b76e628d944095fa"}, "toolResults": []}
