e Java file directly. \\n\\nAlternatively, I could compile a helper Java class to a temporary directory, but the `Class.forName` for `RuntimeMappers` fails. Maybe making `RuntimeMappers` a Java class/object would help, along with the right module symbol flag. For the field fallback, I might need to retrieve the runtime field from a Java object held by a Scala object.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring field fallback options**\\n\\nI'm considering if I can use a Java holder in the temporary `helperClassesDir`, but it seems like objects in the test classes can’t reference that temp area. Could I define a field fallback using a public static class in Scala? However, Scala might only treat public fields as methods, even with `@BeanProperty`. \\n\\nMaybe I could instead use a public field from a Java standard library class, calling `retrieveRuntimeField` on `evalQualJvm(qual1)` and the name. I'm thinking that my object `fieldBackedMapperHolder` could return something like `java.awt`, but I need to ensure that the field is of type `PartialFunction`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_sKHBRKlbrAfvQ9AOJoeH81aU|fc_0de9e442508f38ed016a1155ba0e7c8196ac4ffda9ccb154a9", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/src/test/scala/com_github_plokhotnyuk_jsoniter_scala/jsoniter_scala_macros_3/CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeTest.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets.UTF_8\nimport java.nio.file.Files\nimport java.nio.file.Path\nimport java.util.Comparator\nimport javax.tools.ToolProvider\n", "newText": "import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets.UTF_8\nimport java.nio.file.Files\nimport java.nio.file.Path\nimport java.util.Comparator\n"}, {"oldText": "  def compilesCodecsWhoseNameMappersComeFromRuntimeModuleFields(): Unit = {\n", "newText": "  def compilesCodecsWhoseNameMappersComeFromRuntimeModuleValues(): Unit = {\n"},