al `PartialFunction` calls reflectively:\n\n- `isDefinedAt(false)` hits a library bug in `jvmToTerm` for boxed `false`.\n- Anonymous Scala partial functions expose `apply(Object)` rather than the exact `apply(String)` method that `DirectJvmReflectionMethodCall` looks up.\n\nFixes made in:\n\n`tests/src/com.github.plokhotnyuk.jsoniter-scala/jsoniter-scala-macros_3/2.33.3/src/test/scala/com_github_plokhotnyuk_jsoniter_scala/jsoniter_scala_macros_3/CompileTimeEvalInnerQuoteScopeTest.scala`\n\nChanges:\n- Replaced anonymous `PartialFunction` values with a concrete `RuntimeStringPartialFunctionForQuoteScopeTest`.\n- Its `isDefinedAt` always returns `true`, avoiding the unsupported boxed-`false` compile-time evaluation path.\n- Its `apply(value: String)` has a concrete `String` parameter, matching the reflective lookup.\n- Replaced the holder accessor path with `scala.runtime.ObjectRef.elem`, which is a public field and should exercise the `retrieveRuntimeField` `getField` fallback.\n\nI did not run the tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0de9e442508f38ed016a11561d87e881969b5c5e3715bec5ac\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1050, "output": 693, "cacheRead": 67584, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 69327, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779521045601, "responseId": "resp_0de9e442508f38ed016a115616dd7c819688bf62cc50884278"}}
